          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can retail investors copy the Ikjum Im portfolio?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, but with caveats. Retail investors can view quarterly 13F filings to see institutional holdings, but these are delayed. Attempting to copy exact trades often leads to entering positions much later than the institutions did."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why is the Ikjum Im portfolio performance notable?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Its performance is notable because it frequently demonstrates an ability to capture alpha (excess return) during bull markets while maintaining a lower beta (volatility) during market downturns compared to standard index funds."
          }
        }
      ]
